into nonprofit management and other things and ended up at Congregate a few years ago.

13
00:01:11,145 --> 00:01:16,273
And it's really unexpected to me, all the ways in which my various sort of wayfinding

14
00:01:16,353 --> 00:01:22,803
jobs have all sort of coalesced to make this, to prepare me for what I do now, which I love.

15
00:01:25,120 --> 00:01:30,942
So, in addition to that, there's something you need to know about me, and that's that I'm a storyteller.

16
00:01:31,623 --> 00:01:36,544
If you ask me a question, I will probably respond with a story, and the story has a purpose.

17
00:01:37,545 --> 00:01:44,187
I come from sturdy peasant stock, and one of the values that I got from them is telling stories.

18
00:01:44,367 --> 00:01:50,549
