00:23:00,285 --> 00:23:04,126
I'll tell you a bit about how they handled them, but also hopefully give you some pointers

330
00:23:04,326 --> 00:23:06,806
on how to avoid them in the future.

331
00:23:08,847 --> 00:23:13,028
So first I'd like to talk about the moderate path, which ties back to some of the things

332
00:23:14,488 --> 00:23:17,609
that I was touching on earlier with fairness and lenience.

333
00:23:19,313 --> 00:23:22,715
So a couple years ago now, I got pulled into a situation in a game forum.

334
00:23:23,355 --> 00:23:28,958
A user who I will call Bob, not his real name, as far as I know, had played the game for

335
00:23:29,018 --> 00:23:30,819
quite a while, and then he quit.

336
00:23:32,420 --> 00:23:37,043
But despite having quit, he returned every day to be disruptive.

337
00:23:37,743 --> 00:23:42,326
He would insult the other players, he would talk trash about the game, and he particularly

338
00:23:42,366 --> 00:23:46,028
liked to insult and bait the community manager, who I'll call Amy.

339
00:23:49,336 --> 00:23:53,298
And as I read through the forum post that Bob had made, I began to notice some things.

340
00:23:54,499 --> 00:23:59,062
So to begin with, he was a player who had spent a fair amount of money in the game and

341
00:23:59,122 --> 00:24:00,583
had some trouble getting support.

342
00:24:01,183 --> 00:24:06,006
This guy was a bit of a hothead, and so he grouched about his bad experience in the forums.

343
00:24:07,327 --> 00:24:09,909
So far, all pretty understandable and normal.

344
00:24:12,736 --> 00:24:17,539
Well, here's where things went awry. Instead of expressing concern about Bob's bad experiences,

345
00:24:18,540 --> 00:24:23,523
Amy just removed his posts. Bob responded with angry criticism and she got angry in

346
00:24:23,563 --> 00:24:26,725
return and they got locked in this power struggle, right?

347
00:24:27,685 --> 00:24:33,209
Now Bob was behaving badly and Amy, despite her best intentions, was just feeding that

348
00:24:33,249 --> 00:24:39,533
troll every day. She'd hide his posts, she'd talk about how terrible he was. She was personalizing

349
00:24:39,593 --> 00:24:40,073
away too much.

350
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:44,803
She didn't mean to get into this situation.

351
00:24:44,883 --> 00:24:45,564
I know she didn't.

352
00:24:45,864 --> 00:24:50,109
But she was in an unfortunate situation where she had overreacted initially and then not

353
00:24:50,129 --> 00:24:51,271
really been able to backpedal.

354
00:24:52,993 --> 00:24:58,140
So the way to avoid that is to allow negative feedback within reason.

355
00:24:59,256 --> 00:25:03,960
So the things underneath the heart are the things that I would allow and encourage on

356
00:25:04,020 --> 00:25:04,440
our site.

357
00:25:05,141 --> 00:25:12,006
The things underneath the other, the circle slash, are the things that I would hide and

358
00:25:12,687 --> 00:25:17,530
depending on how routinely the person had been posting stuff like that, I might take

359
00:25:17,551 --> 00:25:21,634
a little bit of action on their account to be like, hey, I meant it when I said stop

360
00:25:21,674 --> 00:25:21,954
saying that.

361
00:25:21,994 --> 00:25:22,174
Thanks.

362
00:25:22,194 --> 00:25:22,254
Bye.

363
00:25:22,434 --> 00:25:22,494
Bye.

