00:25:36,907 --> 00:25:44,413
So back to Bob and Amy. In one of Bob's forum posts, he had asked why this particular game

368
00:25:44,453 --> 00:25:50,577
was still on Kongregate, despite its many flaws, which he described colorfully. Underneath

369
00:25:50,617 --> 00:25:55,701
the snarky comments, there was a legitimate question about Kongregate's policy and approach.

370
00:25:56,322 --> 00:26:00,725
Why do we let games stay on the site? What are our boundaries? And so on and so forth.

371
00:26:01,265 --> 00:26:04,368
So that question was my opening, because that's right in my wheelhouse.

372
00:26:04,728 --> 00:26:07,331
So I chimed in and I'm tricky rodent.

373
00:26:07,852 --> 00:26:09,454
And I answered his question seriously.

374
00:26:10,275 --> 00:26:14,201
He asked some follow-up questions and so did a couple of other players and I answered those

375
00:26:14,261 --> 00:26:15,202
seriously as well.

376
00:26:15,863 --> 00:26:20,609
But I gave him, along with the information, a sense of myself as unruffled and competent.

377
00:26:23,621 --> 00:26:28,967
He at some point made a passing comment that he says, I don't really give a lot of flowers

378
00:26:29,007 --> 00:26:30,529
with my posts, but I'm not lying.

379
00:26:30,649 --> 00:26:31,891
I'm not making stuff up.

380
00:26:32,412 --> 00:26:33,133
I said, that's okay.

381
00:26:33,153 --> 00:26:34,434
I don't expect a lot of flowers.

382
00:26:34,594 --> 00:26:36,256
And I could tell that there was real stuff here.

383
00:26:36,777 --> 00:26:39,641
So this was apparently quite disarming to him.

384
00:26:40,782 --> 00:26:40,922
So

385
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:44,163
This is one of my favorite forum posts of all time.

386
00:26:45,424 --> 00:26:49,770
He goes through a good bit of effort trying to get himself to say something nice, and

387
00:26:49,790 --> 00:26:53,695
he finally manages it, and then says he has to go lie down because it was so much work.

388
00:26:59,690 --> 00:27:04,113
Now, one of the other players responded before I could, and this was something that made

389
00:27:04,153 --> 00:27:09,697
me even more happy, because suddenly they see him in a different way than they have

390
00:27:09,717 --> 00:27:10,278
seen him before.

391
00:27:10,318 --> 00:27:12,239
Until now, they all hated his guts.

392
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:17,884
And they're like, oh, you can be funny, and even kind of nice and reasonable.

393
00:27:19,794 --> 00:27:21,675
And to which of course he was, oh, you can't prove it.

394
00:27:22,035 --> 00:27:27,218
But from then on, things really changed for him and for that forum.

395
00:27:27,658 --> 00:27:32,861
And he and I had a little sort of private side conversations, and he agreed to leave

396
00:27:32,901 --> 00:27:36,162
the forum alone and go off and play his own game.

397
00:27:37,383 --> 00:27:39,264
And in fact, he is still on our site.

